    "Structural analyses on the representation of German organizations and universities, (scientific) age-groups, female researchers, and team size revealed strong differences between the variants examined here.",
    "The ranking and the relation between German institutions is altered, depending on the definition of HCRs.",
    "The analysis of the scientific age and the distribution of scientific age groups revealed that all five variants under examination in this study select-on average -older researchers.",
    "The variant provided by Ioannidis and co-authors almost only selected researchers that have been in the system for at least 15 years and therefore belong to the oldest age group.",
    "Variant-0 also resulted in a HCRs list that contains a large share of oldest (more than 15 years) researchers."
